<div class="container-fluid p-2 m-1 bg-light text-dark">
    <h3 class="text-center">Instructions for Submitting Forms</h3>

    <h5 class="text-center">Welcome {PatientName}</h5>

    <dl>
        <dt>To return to Portal Dashboard landing page click &#39;Exit to Dashboard&#39; button from Top Action Bar or Title.<br />
            &nbsp;</dt>
        <dt>Filling Out Forms</dt>
        <dd>- Select a form from the &#39;Select Forms&#39; list dropdown button.</dd>
        <dd>- Answer all the appropriate queries in the form.</dd>
        <dd>- When finished or wish to edit further later, click &#39;Save as Draft&#39; or when finished with the form click the &#39;Submit Completed&#39; button in top Action Menu. Save Draft will save the currently edited form to your Forms Activity History list and will still be available for editing until you delete the form or send to your clinician using the &#39;Submit Completed&#39; action button.</dd>
        <dt>Sending Forms</dt>
        <dd>- Click the &#39;Submit Completed&#39; button from Action Menu.</dd>
        <dd>- Once sent, the form will show in your &#39;Forms Activity&#39; as In Review. You may still make changes to the form until reviewed by practice administrator where once the review is completed, &#39;Forms Activity&#39; will show the form as Locked and no further edits are available. At this point, your completed document is recorded in your chart (medical record).</dd>
        <dt>Signing Document</dt>
        <dd>- Create, erase or redo your Signature by clicking the &#39;Signature&#39; button in top Actions Menu. You may also manage your signature from the Dashboard.</dd>
        <dd>- To add your signature to a form, simply click the appropriate sign here &#39;X&#39;.</dd>
        <dd>- To remove a signature, click the signature to return to the default sign here &#39;X&#39;.</dd>
    </dl>
</div>
